            <p class="lead"><strong>Oshawa is one of the few Durham Region cities with comprehensive STR regulations.</strong> If you're looking to Airbnb your home in Oshawa, you'll need to understand the licensing requirements, principal residence rules, and the 180-night annual limit.</p>
            <p class="lead">Here's everything you need to know about Oshawa's STR licensing bylaw and how to operate compliantly in 2026.</p>
          </div>

          <h2 id="overview">Oshawa STR Overview</h2>
          <p>Oshawa's short-term rental regulations are governed by Schedule "Q" of the Licensing By-law 122-2024. The city defines a short-term rental as:</p>

          <blockquote class="bylaw-quote">
            "All or part of a dwelling unit that is used to provide temporary accommodation" through a rental company platform, requiring operator licensure.
            <cite>City of Oshawa Licensing By-law 122-2024, Schedule Q</cite>
          </blockquote>

          <p>Oshawa uses <strong>28 days</strong> as the threshold, consistent with most GTA municipalities. Any rental under 28 consecutive days is considered a short-term rental and requires licensing.</p>

