            </div>
          </div>

          <h2 id="compliance">Staying Compliant</h2>
          <p>Oshawa takes enforcement seriously. Here's how to stay on the right side of the bylaw:</p>

          <h3>Record Keeping (6 Years)</h3>
          <p>You must keep detailed records for at least 6 years:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Rental dates and number of nights</li>
            <li>Whether whole-home or room rental</li>
            <li>Confirmation renters received Visitor's Code</li>
            <li>MAT collected (keep 7 years for MAT records)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Advertising Requirements</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Display your valid license number</strong> on all listings and advertisements</li>
            <li>Cannot advertise an STR without a valid license</li>
            <li>Keep listings accurate and up-to-date</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Local Contact</h3>
          <p>Your designated Local Contact must:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Be available <strong>24/7</strong></li>
            <li>Respond within <strong>one hour</strong> by phone or email</li>
            <li>Be able to attend the property if needed</li>
            <li>Have authority to resolve issues</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="penalties">Penalties for Non-Compliance</h2>
          <p>Oshawa enforces STR regulations with escalating penalties:</p>

          <div class="penalty-box">
            <h4>Penalty Structure</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Operating without license:</strong> Up to $500</li>
              <li><strong>Other bylaw violations:</strong> Up to $250</li>
              <li><strong>Provincial Offences Act:</strong> $500 to $100,000</li>
              <li><strong>MAT non-compliance:</strong> 1.25% penalty on first day of default, plus 1.25% monthly interest</li>
              <li><strong>Unpaid amounts:</strong> Can be added to your property tax bill</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <p>The city can also revoke or suspend your license for non-compliance. Corporate officers and directors can be held personally liable for violations.</p>

          <h2 id="official-resources">Official City of Oshawa Resources</h2>
          <p>Always verify current requirements with official sources:</p>

          <div class="resources-box">
            <h4>Official Links</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://www.oshawa.ca/business-development/housing-permits-and-licences/short-term-rentals/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">City of Oshawa STR Licensing</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.oshawa.ca/en/home-property/resources/Documents/STR-Application.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">STR License Application (PDF)</a></li>
